JOHANNESBURG - Home Affairs offices countrywide will be closed on Saturday as negotiations continue with labour unions. The department and unions still haven't found solutions to ensure that offices provide full services on Saturdays.READ: Home Affairs strike avertedAnother round of negotiations is set to begin on Monday.Home Affairs staff threatened strike action when the department tried to force staff to work on Saturdays without being paid overtime.The department is appealing to union leaders to assist in resolving the matter.eNCA